{
  "texts": [
    "From this starting point, the authors have developed several additional contributions.",
    "Gemeinhardt et al.. [56], in a different work, analyze how model-driven optimization techniques can be applied in the context of quantum software.",
    "Furthermore, the same authors propose a modelling language and a design framework for quantum circuits that support the definition of composite operators [58].",
    "This allows developers to raise the abstraction level of quantum algorithm design alongside the provided code generator.",
    "Similarly, Ammermann et al. [14] propose a view-based quantum development approach based on a Single Underlying Model (SUM)."
  ]
}